 of student outrage and unrest, recall the days when blasphemy could be punished by death, and reveal that the university's department of anatomy once supported a thriving trade in body-snatching. Upheaval and crisis, triumph and achievement succeed each other by turns in a story that is entertaining, intriguing and surprising - and always interesting.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aUniversities and collegeszScotlandzEdinburghxHistory. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Robert D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLynch, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLynch, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Shea, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Nicholas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPhillipson, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147446393540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474463935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474463935/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK